citations.desc: Access and inspection of records and property; submission of itineraries.
citations.narrative:
The licensee was unable to find the Program of Veterinary Care. The licensee had a Program of Veterinary Care at the
last inspection, but has since misplaced it. Not being able to produce a Program of Veterinary Care during inspection
doesn't allow for APHIS officials to ensure the animals are being cared for as per the instructions of the Attending
Veterinarian. The licensee must find and produce the Program of Veterinary Care at the next inspection. If the Program
of Veterinary Care can't be found, then the licensee must have the Attending Veterinarian fill out a new Program of
Veterinary Care.
Correct by 4/17/23.
This inspection and exit interview were conducted with the Facility Representative.
End of report.
Additional Inspectors:
CATHERINE HOVANCSAK n
